message: "It is our obligation as Americans to dig deep in doing whatever we can to build the kind of future that we want for ourselves and our children...I want to be sure that when they grow up, our country is still the engine of opportunity with the values that made us great in the first place and that the world is peaceful and prosperous so that they can make the choices that they wish to make to chart their own futures. That is what we believe in here in America. And that is exactly what is on the ballot this election." —Hillary

“We are a nation of Hispanic roots, and that’s a proud part of who we are, and that’s why we have the Mes de la Herencia Hispana, to remember that we’ve always been a Hispanic nation since our very first day.” —Tim Kaine
